= Examples of Major and Minor Shirk
== Major Shirk (Shirk Akbar):

=== 1. Clear Major Shirk:

- Slaughtering for other than Allāh
- Making vows to other than Allāh
- Seeking help from other than Allāh in matters only Allāh can control

=== 2. Hidden Major Shirk:

- The shirk of the hypocrites and their showing off (_riyāʾ_: showing Islām
  outwardly and hiding their disbelief)
- Hidden fear: fearing others besides Allāh in things only Allāh can control

== Minor Shirk (Shirk Asghar):
=== 1. Clear Minor Shirk:

- Swearing by someone other than Allāh

- Saying: “What Allāh wills #sc[AND] you will”
- Saying: “If it weren't for Allāh #sc[AND] so-and-so”

=== 2. Hidden Minor Shirk:

- Slight showing off (_riyāʾ_)
- Believing in bad omens (_ṭiyarah_)

== A Beneficial Duʿāʾ for Protection from Shirk:

Abū Mūsā #pleasedHIM said in a _ḥadīth_,

